.TH "snd_soc_runtime_action" 9 "snd_soc_runtime_action" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_soc_runtime_action \- Increment/Decrement active count for PCM runtime components
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" snd_soc_runtime_action
.BI "(struct snd_soc_pcm_runtime *rtd "  ","
.BI "int stream "  ","
.BI "int action "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rtd" 12
ASoC PCM runtime that is activated
.IP "stream" 12
Direction of the PCM stream
.IP "action" 12
Activate stream if 1. Deactivate if -1.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Increments/Decrements the active count for all the DAIs and components
attached to a PCM runtime.
Should typically be called when a stream is opened.

Must be called with the rtd->card->pcm_mutex being held
